As we remember Rev. Dr. Martin Luther King Jr., we also reflect on the impact of those who marched beside him. We’re proud to have people in the #McFamily like Ron Damper (pictured here) who marched with Dr. King in 1967 to help fight for equality for all Americans.

Ron Damper’s company, DAMRON Corporation, was our first national diverse supplier and continues to supply our hot and cold tea blends to U.S. restaurants.

This week, McDonald’s employees across Chicago will honor Dr. King’s legacy by participating in our very first MLK Week of Service. We’re proud to recognize Dr. King and all those who continue to embody his values. #MLKDay
